    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/result/multi-study-hemolysis-synthesis",
      "type": "uofa:EvidenceItem",
      "name": "Synthesis of hemolysis modeling literature — multi-study aggregated evidence",
      "description": "This evidence node aggregates findings from seven independent CFD hemolysis studies published between 2008 and 2021, including the seminal Goubergrits & Affeld (2004) power-law calibration, the Taskin et al. (2012) comparative turbulence model assessment, the Fraser et al. (2012) FDA pump benchmark, and four subsequent replication studies. The synthesis establishes the epistemic basis for the hemolysis model form and parameter ranges adopted in the present COU. Given the breadth of the literature base and the independent replication across multiple laboratories, the aggregated findings are treated as a robust evidentiary foundation for model form selection."
    },
